
This directory contains scripts for developpers who want to contribute
to this module or simply test it.


Contributing
============

Please follow the coding style guide:

    PEP 0008 -- Style Guide for Python Code
    https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/


Tests
=====

For starters, the examples provided in ~BGWpy/Examples can be used
as a test suite for this module. The script run_examples.sh can be
executed from the Examples directory. The script sync_examples_references.sh
can be executed from the Examples directory to update the reference files.

Automated test can be launched from the top directory using nose,
e.g. (assuming you have installed nose with color plugin):
    nosetests --color

Please note that the examples and the tests have to be maintained
    separately.
